title: Rockefeller Foundation records, Pamphlet File, Series 2
finding_aid_title: A Guide to the Rockefeller Foundation records, Pamphlet File, Series 2
finding_aid_filing_title: Rockefeller Foundation records, Pamphlet File, Series 2

subnotes.content: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

The Rockefeller Foundation Pamphlet Collection consists of 41 archival boxes and approximately 23 cu. ft. of records. The Rockefeller Foundation maintained a vast collection of published pamphlets, academic papers, book manuscripts, magazine articles, and other booklets that reference the Foundation or members of the Rockefeller family or were created by RF leaders, employees, or grantees. The pamphlets date from 1878 to 1988, with the majority containing dates between 1935 and 1975.
The collection is organized alphabetically by author, organization, or major subject, depending on the original classification by the Rockefeller Foundation.

Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at <extref href="http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php">http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php</extref>
